        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Since the Financial Crisis in 2009, that\xe2\x80\x99s mostly flipped. Today, the risk-free rate is at 1.29% while inflation is at 4.31% (based on the Consumer Price Index, whether that\xe2\x80\x99s accurately capturing real inflation is for another conversation). That means that if you invest in 10 Year Treasuries, your money buys 3%
         <em>
          less
         </em>
         every year.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Oaktree\xe2\x80\x99s Howard Marks wrote an excellent memo on this topic back in October titled
         <em>
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkc2OrCAQRp-m2bVBUGgWLGZzX8PwU9qkFQwU1_j2g-1iEkIl9VE5lYMzCEvKp95TQXJdE5476AhHWQERMqkF8hS87gV78XFQxOvB96_xRUKZ5gywmbBqzBXIXu0anMGQ4neCUjaSt54tCDlSq5waxEsw7wbFuLdUCcmo5TfXVB8gOtDwH_KZIpBVvxH38uA_D_avneM4umQ-2JjO7AHN2rm0tcAnV64Cs6krPkuq2UFrbLClK2ivQlyeIWJ6zsnV0u1-JkEzynoqmerZKDjt-k54Ieg8AlVeGdNLkHKUYOlo5l7Oxj0Gui2sK9UWNO5z4UnWMaFNuRFa_HmbDb57XTamVrcaA54TRGNX8LcovH1_1U0LRMjtH_xk8LIs2zIDVXxgt5hmkit-qWekkX1qU_EP-gsRzpiE" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Coming Into Focus
          </a>
          .
         </em>
         If you want to go deep, you should read the whole thing. The takeaway is that lower interest rates have a dramatic impact on every part of the market. When the risk-free rate is lower, returns on all other asset classes come down, too.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; text-align: center;">
         <figure style="display: inline-block; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
